column5: Nice fish Pete !
Nice Pete, off to a great start as usual
For many like me Pete that's a fish of a lifetime. I am so happy you Musky guys are able to get out there finally. Fanatic isn't the word to describe some of you Essox folk.
Beauty fish Pete  Looking to land my first ever muskie this season
nice fish Pete I am heading up to Nipissing for muskie opener this week. I hope I find some as nice as those.  Art
Nice Fish Pete!

After a very very very long wait, it was finally slime time... opening weekend... and there on the Saturday, I sat in class. Whaaaat? Yes class for my apprenticeship program. Sigh. For the long-term good I suppose.  After a few setbacks on Sunday morning, the boys already out and into a bunch of fish, I decided to head out solo for the afternoon. Didn't see a single fish until some nasty weather approached... and as the old saying goes, muskies will eat before a storm! This fish inhaled an entire magnum bulldawg - do you think she was hungry? Getting good solo pics is not the easiest but these turned out pretty darn good. 47" is actually my best opening day fish ever. Gallie - thanks for the tip - this might have just been the fish you guys saw!  Cheers Pete
damn pete, thats a clean one, way shinier than the old rotten hog i nabbed with ya in the fall.  I swear to god pete, you put more muskies in the boat than some people put eyes.
She 's a beauty.
Noice!  And magazines say downsize early season lmao  MAG DAWG!!!!
Well done there bud. I cant wait for the musky season bait fish to open soon.LOL  Good job.
No worries pete! If we couldnt have her im glad you were the one to land her! And i thought i would get laughed at for throwing big rubber around on opener but thats all they would touch.
Nice fish! I kept on bringing in pike after pike on my 9" shadzilla.  I didn't see anyone else out throwing big rubber.
That's a nice looking fish ... The pics turned out great .
I hope some of those pike made it to your dinner plate! That's a beauty way to start the season Pete. We had a good day out too (4 for 6) but I would trade them all for that one!
Just another day at the office eh Pete!
Beauty fish!
Putting in work as always! Good stuff buddy
Nice fish great way to start the season
Nice one!! Got me itching to get out there...
Noice!  And magazines say downsize early season lmao  MAG DAWG!!!!   And fish cant read especially muskies, they always say match the hatch too, but many times go against the masses for results
That is a thing of beauty...I can see why you are admiring it.
Nice fish Pete!
Great fish! So clean too!
Nice fish!

Thanks all. Might sneak out somewhere tomorrow morning to try get another!
